 within recommended guidelines. Keep it up!","alert_housing_over":"You're spending {pct}% ({amount}) on housing — try to keep it within {recommended} ({recommendedAmount}). This prevents being \"house poor\" and frees cash for savings.","alert_savings_under":"You're only saving {pct}% ({amount}) — aim for at least {recommended} ({recommendedAmount}). The 50/30/20 rule suggests at least 20% toward savings and debt repayment.","alert_food_over":"Food is at {pct}% ({amount}) — try to keep it within {recommended} ({recommendedAmount}). Cooking at home more often can help bring this down.","alert_transport_over":"Transport at {pct}% ({amount}) exceeds the recommended {recommended} ({recommendedAmount}). Consider carpooling, public transit, or optimizing routes.","alert_utilities_over":"Utilities at {pct}% ({amount}) are above the typical {recommended} range ({recommendedAmount}). Review subscriptions and energy usage for potential savings.","alert_entertainment_over":"Entertainment is at {pct}% ({amount}) — aim for {recommended} ({recommendedAmount}). Make sure essentials and savings are covered first.","alert_disclaimer":"Based on the 50/30/20 rule. These are general guidelines, not financial advice — your ideal split depends on your personal situation."}